  "user_text": "The SoKnow process begins with the HR department organizing employee interviews.\n\nFirst, appointment suggestions are sent.\n\nThen, the process branches: on one side, the employee interview is conducted, during which training is assigned, and on the other side, regular inquiries are made to ensure progress.\n\nSimultaneously, the employee must confirm the appointment, participate in the interview, and complete the training.\n\nFinally, the training is completed, and the employee interview is marked as conducted.",
  "output_text": "The process begins with organizing employee interviews. Once the interviews are organized, appointment suggestions are sent out. After sending the appointment suggestions, the process splits into three parallel activities that occur simultaneously.\n\nThe first activity is conducting the employee interview. Once the interview is conducted, the next step is to assign training to the employee.\n\nThe second activity involves making regular inquiries. This activity continues until it converges with the other parallel activities.\n\nThe third activity is confirming the appointment. After the appointment is confirmed, the employee participates in the interview. Following the interview, the employee completes the assigned training.\n\nOnce all three parallel activities are completed, the process reaches a decision point. At this point, there are two possible outcomes:\n\n1. If the training is completed, the process moves to mark the training as completed.\n2. Alternatively, the process can proceed to mark the interview as conducted.\n\nAfter either marking the training as completed or marking the interview as conducted, the process concludes."
